WEBVTT

00:55.189 --> 00:57.625
[ Splattering sound ]

02:15.703 --> 02:19.640
* [ Woman Vocalizing ]

03:53.534 --> 03:56.103
[ Man shouts ]

03:56.136 --> 03:58.572
[ Woman ]
Mirror, mirror,
on the wall,

03:58.606 --> 04:01.074
who's the fairest
of us all ?

04:01.108 --> 04:03.711
You're the fairest
in this hall,

04:03.744 --> 04:06.347
but snow white
is the--

04:06.380 --> 04:08.949
[ Chuckles ]
Come on, rebecca.
Forget it's a play.

04:08.982 --> 04:11.385
Just say it like
you're saying it to me.

04:11.419 --> 04:14.254
Snow white's
the fairest of them all.
And again.

04:14.288 --> 04:17.257
Mirror, mirror, on the wall,
who's the fairest
of us all ?

04:17.291 --> 04:19.560
You're the
fairest in--
wrong.

04:19.593 --> 04:21.728
You are.

04:23.030 --> 04:24.998
What are they doing,
mommy ?

04:26.934 --> 04:29.069
Nothing,
rebecca.

04:29.102 --> 04:32.039
Daddy's gonna be home soon.
Last to the car's
a bag of rats !

04:32.072 --> 04:33.974
[ Dog barking ]

04:34.007 --> 04:37.678
[ Rebecca ]
You never knew
I was a bag of rats !

05:02.370 --> 05:03.771
[ Rebecca ]
Daddy !

05:03.804 --> 05:06.540
Daddy !
[ Barking ]

05:06.574 --> 05:10.778
Hey.
Hey, sweetie.

05:10.811 --> 05:13.414
[ Rebecca ]
The goldfish died.
Oh, no.

05:13.447 --> 05:16.350
He did ?
He started
to swim backwards.

05:16.384 --> 05:20.287
Mom put him in the freezer
and said that we can bury him
when you come back. Okay.

05:20.320 --> 05:23.090
You want something to eat ?
Breakfast and lunch.

05:23.123 --> 05:25.092
Mary's made spaghetti,
I think.
Oh, god.

05:25.125 --> 05:29.196
It's 2:00 in the morning
for me, honey.
I'm sorry.

05:29.229 --> 05:31.064
What are these ?
Nothing.

05:31.098 --> 05:32.400
That's snow white.
Hey,

05:32.433 --> 05:34.502
why don't you show daddy
your fairy costume, honey ?

05:34.535 --> 05:37.605
No, I don't want to.
I wanna show him
the goldfish.

05:37.638 --> 05:40.908
Okay.
[ Chuckles ]

05:40.941 --> 05:43.644
What is this ?
Little red riding hood ?

05:43.677 --> 05:46.146
No. it's nothing
to do with anything.

05:46.179 --> 05:49.016
It's just another
weird dream.

05:49.049 --> 05:52.786
Oh, no. not like
the one you had before
my mother died, is it ?

05:52.820 --> 05:54.254
No.
Good.

05:54.287 --> 05:57.090
Not like that one. This one,
it keeps coming back.

05:58.158 --> 06:02.396
There's an orchard
and this little girl.

06:02.430 --> 06:05.866
That little girl,
she's being led through it.

06:05.899 --> 06:09.002
The little girl
that's missing ?
She's holding
someone's hand.

06:09.036 --> 06:12.440
It's a man
or a woman...

06:12.473 --> 06:15.208
With red hair.

06:15.242 --> 06:19.480
I keep trying to get
rid of it. I can't.

06:19.513 --> 06:20.881
I don't know.
What do you want me to say ?

06:20.914 --> 06:24.117
If it's real,
you should go to the cops.
Come on, paul, please.

06:24.151 --> 06:27.588
I don't know what to do
with this psychic stuff.
I hate that word.

06:27.621 --> 06:30.223
So do I.
What's "physic,"
Daddy ?

06:30.257 --> 06:31.358
They're searching
the reservoir,

06:31.391 --> 06:33.794
but I have a feeling
she's not dead.

06:34.695 --> 06:36.797
What's "physic," Daddy ?

06:36.830 --> 06:40.501
Psychic is when you can
see through things, like,

06:40.534 --> 06:43.471
what's in that
big, big, big box
that daddy brought home ?

06:43.504 --> 06:45.973
[ Shouting ]
Right by
the front door.

06:46.006 --> 06:47.441
You got it ?
You bet ya.

06:47.475 --> 06:50.377
I tramped
all over tokyo for that.

06:50.410 --> 06:53.814
[ Motor whining ]

06:53.847 --> 06:56.416
[ Paul ]
Not too low.

06:58.686 --> 07:00.554
And again.
[ Chuckles ]

07:10.163 --> 07:12.900
[ Whispers ]
Good night, sweetheart.

07:12.933 --> 07:15.636
Wasn't that meant
for her birthday?

07:15.669 --> 07:17.337
Yeah, it was.

07:17.370 --> 07:20.140
But I can't be here.
I'm only on a stopover.

07:20.173 --> 07:22.442
Have you told her ?
No.

07:22.476 --> 07:24.645
They fucked up
my schedule again.

07:24.678 --> 07:27.548
What about the play ?
No, no.
The play's fine.

07:27.581 --> 07:29.950
I have to leave
for Seattle at 8:00.

07:38.191 --> 07:39.960
Hey. I got you
a kimono.

07:41.094 --> 07:42.496
[ Growls ]

07:52.272 --> 07:55.576
[ Dog barking ]

07:58.045 --> 08:00.080
Hey.

08:32.980 --> 08:34.948
[ Girl ]
What did you say
your name was ?

08:34.982 --> 08:36.448
[ Deep voice ]
Red.

08:40.821 --> 08:43.222
[ GIRL: Indistinct ]

08:44.825 --> 08:47.160
[ Sighing ]

08:49.797 --> 08:52.666
[ Girl ]
Where are we going ?

08:56.469 --> 08:59.206
[ Gasps ]

08:59.239 --> 09:01.041
[ Sobbing ]

09:01.074 --> 09:03.476
What ?

09:03.510 --> 09:05.879
What is it ?

09:07.648 --> 09:11.418
I saw her, the little girl
that's missing.

09:11.451 --> 09:14.888
I can't help it.
I'm sorry.
Oh, Jesus.

09:14.922 --> 09:16.957
I'm sorry.

09:21.261 --> 09:23.997
She's so innocent, Paul,

09:24.031 --> 09:26.433
going wherever he asks her.

09:27.467 --> 09:29.536
It's somewhere terrible.

09:29.569 --> 09:32.539
I told you, if it's real,
you should go to the cops.

09:34.374 --> 09:35.442
It's worse now.

09:35.475 --> 09:38.679
It's like some storm's
about to break.

09:39.246 --> 09:41.048
All right, look, honey.

09:41.081 --> 09:43.450
Tomorrow I'll go
to the police, okay ?

09:43.483 --> 09:47.087
I'll tell them whatever
it is you're imagining
you're seeing, all right ?

09:47.120 --> 09:49.690
I wanna know I'm wrong, Paul,
more than anything.

09:49.723 --> 09:52.760
I wanna know
it's just a dream.

09:54.194 --> 09:56.964
[ Paul sighs ]

09:56.997 --> 10:00.000
Oh, you know,
I'm sorry to keep you
waiting, Mr. Cooper.

10:00.033 --> 10:03.203
I apologize.
Really I do.
No problem.

10:03.236 --> 10:06.573
I hope you understand that,
you know, this is, well--

10:06.606 --> 10:09.442
I mean, this has been
a very busy week.
Yeah, yeah.

10:09.476 --> 10:11.945
Okay, uh, let me--

10:11.979 --> 10:14.414
let me see if
I get this right here.

10:14.447 --> 10:18.251
Your wife
had a headache...

10:18.285 --> 10:20.220
And she saw a vision
of the missing child,
is that right ?

10:20.253 --> 10:22.622
No, no. I wouldn't
phrase it like that.

10:22.656 --> 10:25.793
How would you phrase it ?
She has, um--
she has these dreams.

10:25.826 --> 10:28.095
Dreams.
Is she a clairvoyant ?
No.

10:28.128 --> 10:30.664
Does she, you know,
talk to dead people ?
What ?

10:30.698 --> 10:32.365
Does she communicate
with the dead ?
No.

10:32.399 --> 10:34.668
Detective,
this isn't something
out of a seance.

10:34.702 --> 10:37.671
'Cause I was gonna ask you,
does she wear a turban ?
[ Laughs ]

10:37.705 --> 10:40.607
One of those crystal balls
with a lamp shade.
None of that ?

10:40.640 --> 10:42.542
None of that.
Just checking.

10:42.575 --> 10:44.277
All right,
tell me what happened.

10:44.311 --> 10:47.380
She had a dream that
the child was taken
to an apple orchard...

10:47.414 --> 10:51.118
Where some terrible things
were happenin' to her,
somewhere north of here.

10:51.151 --> 10:53.186
Oh, yeah ?
Yeah.

10:53.220 --> 10:56.790
In this vision of hers,
did she get a fix
on anyone else ?

10:56.824 --> 10:59.592
Only his hand.
He was holding
her hand.

10:59.626 --> 11:01.528
You mean,
the little girl ?

11:01.561 --> 11:03.797
Yeah, but then she
did say it could've
been a woman's.

11:03.831 --> 11:06.066
Could have been-- oh.
Yeah.

11:06.099 --> 11:08.101
All right. okay.
Okay, sir.

11:08.135 --> 11:11.271
Thanks for comin' in.
Detective,
hang on a second !

11:11.304 --> 11:14.307
I'm waitin' here an hour.
I don't think my wife
is makin' this up.

11:14.341 --> 11:15.642
I'm not saying
she's makin' it up.

11:15.675 --> 11:18.145
It's been a long day,
so give me a break.

11:18.178 --> 11:22.249
Based on your information,
I'm lookin' for a man,
I'm lookin' for a woman.

11:22.282 --> 11:24.117
It's not really
helpin' me out.
Listen.

11:24.151 --> 11:27.320
Listen, listen.
I know you guys
got a tough job alright,

11:27.354 --> 11:30.090
I got a tough job too.
I fly 747s.

11:30.123 --> 11:32.760
Oh ?
I got 350 people relyin'
on me for their lives.

11:32.793 --> 11:36.463
So do me a favor, just
hear me out. Don't treat me
like I'm some kind of wacko.

11:36.496 --> 11:37.998
They already found her,
Mr. Cooper.

11:38.031 --> 11:42.435
Bottom of a storm drain.
Stones in her pockets.

11:42.469 --> 11:44.838
So you go back
to flyin' your 747s.

11:44.872 --> 11:47.074
You take care
of your people.

11:47.107 --> 11:48.641
I gotta get back to the
tedious business of

11:48.675 --> 11:51.411
finding the fuck
who killed her.

11:51.444 --> 11:53.113
Thanks for comin' in.

11:59.019 --> 12:01.154
[ Rebecca ]
There are 12 fairies, Mommy.

12:01.188 --> 12:04.091
Oh. but you'll
look the best.

12:04.124 --> 12:05.959
I'm the only one
that talks.

12:05.993 --> 12:08.796
Okay. why don't you
try it one more time ?

12:08.829 --> 12:12.499
Then we'll go to
dance class, okay ?
Big breath.

12:12.532 --> 12:14.734
Who's the fairest
of us all ?

12:14.768 --> 12:17.170
You're the fairest
in this hall,

12:17.204 --> 12:21.441
but snow white's
the fairest of them all.

12:21.474 --> 12:22.843
Very good.

12:25.112 --> 12:26.346
[ Paul ]
Claire ?

12:28.648 --> 12:30.050
Hon ?

12:38.058 --> 12:39.626
There you are.

12:39.659 --> 12:42.562
You don't have to tell me.
I heard it on the news.

12:43.730 --> 12:45.799
Guess I'm crazy again,
huh ?

12:47.067 --> 12:50.370
Well, you got it wrong
this time.

12:50.403 --> 12:52.372
Yeah, I got a lot
of things wrong.

12:53.941 --> 12:57.244
What's that supposed to mean ?
You know exactly
what it means.

12:57.277 --> 12:58.611
No, I don't.
What are you talking about ?

12:58.645 --> 13:02.015
I'm talking about
the girl that you're seeing
in sydney, Australia.

13:03.917 --> 13:07.921
I'm talking about
me pretending
it hasn't been happening.

13:07.955 --> 13:11.158
Don't look so surprised,
either. I'm not
reading your mind.

13:11.191 --> 13:12.792
I'm not reading your
fucking letters, either,

13:12.826 --> 13:14.661
but you should be
more discreet
where you put them !

13:14.694 --> 13:18.131
It fell in Rebecca's lap.
I took this girl
out to dinner once.

13:18.165 --> 13:21.501
She got a crush on me.
I fucked up. I'm sorry.

13:21.534 --> 13:24.304
Nothing happened.
Honey, listen to me.

13:24.337 --> 13:28.041
Nothing happened.
I promise you.
I fucked up.

13:28.075 --> 13:30.177
So this is what's been
fucking up the schedule ?

13:30.210 --> 13:33.013
No, this is not what's been
fucking up the schedule.

13:33.046 --> 13:35.849
My schedule changes
without notice, how many times
do I have to tell you that?

13:35.883 --> 13:38.285
This isn't about
your schedule. This is about
you fucking someone.

13:38.318 --> 13:41.488
But I didn't fuck anyone !
I wanted to, but I didn't !

13:43.924 --> 13:45.725
Maybe I wouldn't
have wanted to...

13:45.758 --> 13:49.162
If the woman I love
could at least be here
once in a while !

13:49.196 --> 13:52.132
I mean, where the hell
are you, Claire ?

13:52.165 --> 13:55.668
If it's not one obsession,
it's another. you're gone.

13:55.702 --> 13:59.172
Daddy,
if I was real,
Hmm?

13:59.206 --> 14:01.108
Dishing out wishes,
All right.

14:01.141 --> 14:03.243
What would you wish ?

14:03.276 --> 14:06.046
That I didn't
need one.

14:07.714 --> 14:09.016
Okay, let's go.

14:09.049 --> 14:12.085
My wand cured the rain.
Oh, thank god for that.

14:12.119 --> 14:14.955
Let me take these off
because they'll get bent
in the car. okay ?

14:14.988 --> 14:18.225
Are you coming ?
Yes, yes, I'm coming
in the other car.

14:18.258 --> 14:19.893
Okay, let's go.
Why ?

14:19.927 --> 14:21.995
Because I have to fly
tonight, darlin'.

14:22.029 --> 14:24.197
When I come back,
I'll stay much longer.

14:24.965 --> 14:26.633
If your mother lets me.

14:28.401 --> 14:31.104
Hello, flowers.

14:31.138 --> 14:32.940
Hello, birds.

14:32.973 --> 14:34.975
Hello, snow white !
[ Screams ]

14:35.008 --> 14:38.878
Please don't kill me.
I'm begging you. Please.

14:38.912 --> 14:42.349
What have I done ?
Please don't kill me.

14:42.382 --> 14:44.784
Please show mercy!

14:44.817 --> 14:47.420
ALL: Please show mercy!

14:47.454 --> 14:49.957
ALL: Please show mercy !

14:49.990 --> 14:53.226
-ALL: Please show mercy !
- run !

14:53.260 --> 14:55.828
Run into the forest
and never come back,

14:55.862 --> 14:57.931
or your stepmother
will get you !

14:57.965 --> 14:59.199
[ Applause ]

14:59.232 --> 15:02.569
I'll always remember
her beautiful smile.

15:04.004 --> 15:06.039
She was
so very kind.

15:06.073 --> 15:09.542
She made our house
a home.
She was very nice to us.

15:09.576 --> 15:11.678
She so loved animals.
[ Crying ]

15:11.711 --> 15:13.413
She cleaned my glasses.

15:13.446 --> 15:15.348
Honey !
Who is this
lovely maiden ?

15:15.382 --> 15:18.218
Oops!
ALL: She's snow white!

15:18.251 --> 15:19.452
What happened to her ?

15:19.486 --> 15:22.956
[ Dwarves ]
She got poisoned by the witch.

15:22.990 --> 15:25.792
She is the most loveliest
maiden I've ever seen.

15:25.825 --> 15:27.660
May I take her home
to my castle so I can--

15:27.694 --> 15:30.998
will we never
see her again ?

15:31.031 --> 15:33.733
You may come and live
in my castle as well.

15:34.301 --> 15:36.603
[ Applause ]

15:36.636 --> 15:38.538
Mirror, mirror,

15:38.571 --> 15:40.940
on the wall,

15:40.974 --> 15:45.445
who's the fairest
one of all ?

15:45.478 --> 15:49.382
You are the fairest
in this hall,

15:49.416 --> 15:51.718
but snow white
is the fairest...

15:51.751 --> 15:53.520
Of them all.
[ Giggles ]

15:54.787 --> 15:56.889
No, no, no !

15:58.525 --> 16:02.262
Snow white's
the fairest of them all !

16:02.295 --> 16:04.497
[ Screaming ]

16:04.531 --> 16:08.901
[ Giggling, shouting ]

16:08.935 --> 16:10.737
Hello.
There you are.

16:10.770 --> 16:15.075
You were so good.
You were so good.
Okay, hang on a second.

16:15.108 --> 16:18.078
I'll see you in
a couple days, okay ?
All right, bye-bye.

16:18.111 --> 16:19.879
Bye. all right,
already.

16:19.912 --> 16:21.281
I gotta go.

16:24.284 --> 16:26.753
Look, Claire.
I was stupid,
all right ?

16:26.786 --> 16:29.456
I admit that.
Nothing more.
I promise.

16:29.489 --> 16:33.026
Okay.
Promise ?
It was my fault.

16:33.060 --> 16:34.994
Bye, bye.
See you in
a couple days.

16:35.028 --> 16:36.929
I love you.
I gotta go.
All right.

16:39.599 --> 16:41.301
I love you.

16:44.837 --> 16:47.240
[ Engine starts ]

16:50.977 --> 16:55.148
[ Girls shouting ]
Rebecca, Sweetie?

16:55.182 --> 16:57.517
Sorry, I thought you
were my little girl.

16:58.118 --> 16:59.219
Honey.

17:00.853 --> 17:02.489
Rebecca?

17:04.022 --> 17:06.959
[ Shouting ]

17:06.992 --> 17:10.430
Rebecca? Rebecca?

17:10.463 --> 17:12.898
rebecca ?
[ Shouting ]

17:15.402 --> 17:16.769
Rebecca!

17:20.540 --> 17:21.907
Rebecca?

17:26.613 --> 17:27.614
Rebecca!

17:29.582 --> 17:31.784
Rebecca!

17:31.818 --> 17:33.153
Rebecca !

17:33.186 --> 17:34.454
[ Sighing in anguish ]
Rebecca!

17:34.487 --> 17:37.056
[ Girl ]
Where are we going ?

17:38.525 --> 17:39.959
[ Deep voice ]
To my house.

17:41.728 --> 17:44.331
[ Claire ]
Rebecca !

17:44.364 --> 17:46.266
[ Man ]
Guys, fan out to the right !

17:46.299 --> 17:48.468
Rebecca!

17:48.501 --> 17:50.503
Where are you ?
We'll find her.

17:50.537 --> 17:52.539
Rebecca !

17:52.572 --> 17:56.709
Why didn't I know ?
Why didn't I see it ?
Rebecca !

17:57.177 --> 18:00.580
Rebecca !

18:00.613 --> 18:05.352
Rebecca !
[ Man ] I said, you guys
fan out to the right!

18:05.385 --> 18:08.688
Watch your feet.
We're gonna cover every inch
of this ground tonight !

18:08.721 --> 18:12.292
Rebecca !
Rebecca !

18:12.325 --> 18:14.394
Rebecca !

18:16.863 --> 18:20.433
[ Gasps, sobs ]

18:25.104 --> 18:28.107
Why didn't you tell me
it wasn't the past,
It was the future!

18:28.141 --> 18:29.509
Take it easy,
ma'am...

18:29.542 --> 18:32.179
She's gone,
you know that?

18:32.212 --> 18:35.515
We don't know that.
Well, I know it !

18:42.889 --> 18:45.825
Oh, Lord!

18:45.858 --> 18:47.660
Lord, let me help her.

18:48.361 --> 18:51.331
Let me help her!

18:51.364 --> 18:55.034
[SIGHING]

18:55.067 --> 18:57.504
[Deep VOICE: Slow, indistinct]

19:05.845 --> 19:08.915
[Police RADIO: Indistinct]

19:12.151 --> 19:14.721
So how long have you had
these visions, Mrs. Cooper?

19:14.754 --> 19:17.490
All my life.
All your life?

19:19.192 --> 19:20.693
Jeez.

19:20.727 --> 19:24.764
Look, you know, I--
I owe you an apology.
I'm sorry.

19:24.797 --> 19:28.968
Your husband came to
the station to talk to me.
Don't apologize, detective.

19:29.001 --> 19:32.905
No. I was more wrong
than you were.

19:32.939 --> 19:34.374
You see...

19:34.407 --> 19:37.544
I need an interpreter.
For what?.

19:37.577 --> 19:39.412
For whatever the hell
it is I dream.

19:42.715 --> 19:43.950
Hmm.

20:19.719 --> 20:21.220
[ Gasps ]
[Man over police radio]
Detective kay?

20:21.254 --> 20:23.189
Yeah, this is Kay.

20:23.222 --> 20:25.325
- The divers have requested--
-[Sobbing]
-Mrs.--

20:25.358 --> 20:29.228
-Mrs. Cooper--
-Are you there?

20:29.262 --> 20:32.699
Mrs. Cooper, you okay?
Somebody stay with
Mrs. Cooper!

20:32.732 --> 20:35.602
Yeah ?
We found a body.

20:35.635 --> 20:38.271
[Man on police radio
continues, indistinct]

20:41.608 --> 20:43.943
Kay: But, don't touch
any evidence

20:43.976 --> 20:47.447
Everybody, settle down.
Where's Mrs. Cooper?

20:51.851 --> 20:53.386
[ Tires screech ]

20:59.158 --> 21:00.293
Claire.
Paul.

21:00.327 --> 21:03.029
What ?
I can't.
I'm sorry.

21:03.062 --> 21:05.898
I'm sorry.
I-- I--

21:05.932 --> 21:08.468
Oh, God.

21:08.501 --> 21:12.339
Oh, no!
Oh, please, God!

21:12.372 --> 21:15.442
Mr. Cooper,
stay calm.
Is it my daughter?

21:15.475 --> 21:17.577
Is it my daughter?
Stay with us, Mr. Cooper.

21:19.746 --> 21:20.880
Kay!

21:22.315 --> 21:23.483
Wait!

21:26.052 --> 21:28.054
[ Engine racing ]

21:29.121 --> 21:31.190
[ Tires squealing ]

21:49.108 --> 21:50.410
[Siren]

21:50.443 --> 21:53.045
Claire! Please pull over!

21:53.079 --> 21:57.350
